article.description: Walter Whyte had 17 points to lead five Boston University players in double figures as the Terriers narrowly beat Dartmouth 78-76 on Saturday to end a five-game skid.
article.headline: Whyte, Mahoney carry Boston U. over Dartmouth 78-76
article.linkText: Whyte, Mahoney carry Boston U. over Dartmouth 78-76
article.story: BOSTON -- Walter Whyte had 17 points to lead five Boston University players in double figures as the Terriers narrowly beat Dartmouth 78-76 on Saturday to end a five-game skid. Max Mahoney added 16 points, Javante McCoy chipped in 14 with eight assists, Jonas Harper scored 12 points and Alex Vilarino had 10 for the Terriers (4-7). Dartmouth closed to 77-76 on Taurus Samuels' layup with six seconds to go, but McCoy made one of two free throws to ice it. Taurus Samuels scored a career-high 22 points for the Big Green (6-5). James Foye added 17 points and Chris Knight had 11. Boston University plays UMass Lowell on the road next Saturday. Dartmouth matches up against Central Connecticut at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
